guing that there is a care crisis even in the supposedly feminist Nordic ‘nirvana’, this book explores understandings of the care crisis, the serious consequences for gender equality and the hitherto neglected effects on the long-term sustainability of the Nordic welfare states. This astute take on the Nordic welfare model provides insights into what the Nordic experience can tell us about wider international issues in care.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aCaregiverszScandinavia. 0aWelfare statezScandinavia. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Services & Welfare.2bisacsh1 aBjørnholt, Margunn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDahl, Hanne Marlene, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDahl, Hanne Marlene, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHansen, Lise Lotte, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHansen, Lise Lotte, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHoppania, Hanna-Kaisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHorn, Laura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHorn, Laura, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJensen, Carsten Juul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKovalainen, Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLjunggren, Birgitte, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNielsen, Steen Baagøe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNäre, Lena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOlakivi, Antero, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStranz, Anneli, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov